<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="cbcc2eca-e4e2-4401-a11a-69362006431c" >

    <h2>Ryerson student trainees working at external placement employers</h2> 
<p>When a Ryerson student trainee is placed at an external placement employer as part of an unpaid work placement with their approved program, Ryerson is considered a “training agency”.</p> 
<p>In this section you will learn about:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>responsibilities of Ryerson placement coordinators;</li> 
 <li>responsibilities of Ryerson student trainees;</li> 
 <li>insurance eligibility, coverage and duration; and</li> 
 <li>the process for incident or injury reporting.</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#cbcc2eca-e4e2-4401-a11a-69362006431c");});</script></div>

				

				
