            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1537281732179-responsibilities-for-ryerson-placement-coordinators" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1537281732179-responsibilities-for-ryerson-placement-coordinators" aria-controls="accordion-content-1537281732179-responsibilities-for-ryerson-placement-coordinators" aria-expanded="false">
                            Responsibilities for Ryerson placement coordinators
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1537281732179-responsibilities-for-ryerson-placement-coordinators" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1537281732179-responsibilities-for-ryerson-placement-coordinators">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1537281732179 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="5a44f6f0-adec-4a8c-b31b-1abec9f3be9a" >

    <p>A placement coordinator at Ryerson is the person who arranges, coordinates or administers the arrangement of practicum experience placements for student trainee. In some cases, the placement coordinator may also serve as the placement supervisor, adviser, site supervisor and/or practicum supervisor. For a full description, please refer to the definition above.</p> 
<p>As outlined by Ryerson’s Office of the Legal Counsel and Board Secretariat, Ryerson placement coordinators are required to <strong>follow these steps prior to the placement start date</strong>:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Provide the <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1OTToFWBzBZkKYuJawU8iHSI6-8wrh3Md2c_oMa4vAzQ">Letter to Placement Employers<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> to the placement employer to complete. Once it has been completed, provide it to the student trainee to review and sign.</li> 
 <li>Provide the <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1-YKQl0CSu30G3-AB29coQ-XtoZZ0eJjrgX2cLOZZwAg">Student Declaration of Understanding<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> to the student trainee to sign.</li> 
 <li>Send both the completed and signed Letter of Placement Employers and Student Declaration of Understanding to <a href="mailto:practicumwsibform@ryerson.ca">practicumwsibform@ryerson.ca</a>.</li> 
 <li>Determine whether MTCU or Ryerson will be providing the insurance coverage to the student.&nbsp; 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong>If MTCU is providing insurance coverage</strong>, determine whether the placement employer is covered by the WSIA or not. This information can be found on the completed Letter to Placement Employers. If the placement employer is not covered by the WSIA, the number of students that are not covered will be collected quarterly.&nbsp;</li> 
   <li><strong>If Ryerson is providing the insurance coverage</strong>, notify Ryerson’s risk and insurance officer at 416-979-5000, ext. 553772 or <a href="mailto:insurance@ryerson.ca">insurance@ryerson.ca</a> to inform them of the number of students that are not covered by MTCU and require insurance.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Provide a copy of the <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=1KxIpk2X4AYC3mtvisVv0TNPuK_mfprDaWciKT-UYSf4">Pre-placement Risk Assessment Checklist<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> to the placement employer to complete. 
  <ul> 
   <li>This pre-placement tool helps Ryerson University exercise due diligence and ensure that student trainees are not placed in unsafe working environments. It supports the placement employer in an &nbsp;evaluation of the potential risks and safety practices of placement employer.</li> 
   <li><strong>Note</strong>: Only one checklist per academic program per external placement employer is required.. It is also possible to adjust how frequently this checklist is administered and the number of sections requiring completion depending on the placement. For example, for a program that is offered repeatedly by the same employer, the checklist may only need to be completed once a year.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Request that the placement employer complete the <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=189wLwDc9uUCqswiVEc41MW8fiCWLSZj-7jwQDF-45po">Safety Orientation Checklist for Students Working at External Placement Employers<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, used to provide health and safety information to a student prior to work. This is only required if the placement employer does not have their own orientation checklist.</li> 
 <li>In the case that a student trainee has been involved in an incident or injury, immediately upon learning of the incident, the placement coordinator should follow the steps below under “Reporting an incident or injury”.</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
