<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f713e4df-0bce-43c8-b489-3f44e6f0d25f" >

    <p>As outlined by Ryerson's Office of the Legal Counsel and Board Secretariat, students trainee should:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Complete the <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-YKQl0CSu30G3-AB29coQ-XtoZZ0eJjrgX2cLOZZwAg"><span class="sr-only">google doc</span>Student Declaration of Understanding<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-word-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>, sign it and return it to your placement coordinator.</li> 
 <li>Complete Ryerson’s mandatory online safety training.<br> <strong>To access the training:</strong> 
  <ul> 
   <li><a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/d2l-elearning-instructions.html">Follow these enrollment instructions</a>.</li> 
   <li>Select “EHS Training for External Placement Students” in D2L and complete the module.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li><p>Attend any site-specific training required by the placement employer.</p> </li> 
 <li><p>In the event of a workplace incident or injury during the placement, notify your external placement supervisor and the Ryerson placement coordinator.</p> </li> 
</ol>
    





