            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1537281792627-responsibilities-of-student-trainee" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1537281792627-responsibilities-of-student-trainee" aria-controls="accordion-content-1537281792627-responsibilities-of-student-trainee" aria-expanded="false">
                            Responsibilities of student trainee
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1537281792627-responsibilities-of-student-trainee" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1537281792627-responsibilities-of-student-trainee">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1537281792627 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="40deb106-2376-4b2a-ac29-cc1dac43d0e4" >

    <p>The student trainee is required to:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Complete the Student Declaration of Understanding form (to be provided by the student trainee’s institution).</li> 
 <li>Complete all of the following mandatory training: 
  <ul> 
   <li>Ryerson <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/environmental-health-safety-elearning.html">Environmental Health and Safety eLearning</a> (online training);</li> 
   <li>Ryerson <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/whmis.html">Workplace Hazardous Materials Information System (WHMIS)</a> (online training); and</li> 
   <li>other site- or hazard-specific training required on the job as per their Ryerson supervisor.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>In the event of a workplace incident or injury during the placement, notify their Ryerson supervisor and the student trainee’s institution placement coordinator.</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#40deb106-2376-4b2a-ac29-cc1dac43d0e4");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1537281805049-responsibilities-of-ryerson-placement-coordinators" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1537281805049-responsibilities-of-ryerson-placement-coordinators" aria-controls="accordion-content-1537281805049-responsibilities-of-ryerson-placement-coordinators" aria-expanded="false">
                            Responsibilities of Ryerson placement coordinators
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1537281805049-responsibilities-of-ryerson-placement-coordinators" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1537281805049-responsibilities-of-ryerson-placement-coordinators">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1537281805049 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f40e3577-92fe-4896-80df-af2d6d6fd273" >

    <p>Prior to the placement start date, the Ryerson placement coordinator is required to:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Receive the following from the student trainee’s institution:
  <ul> 
   <li>student trainee’s full name (or a list of trainees if multiple trainees is coming from one training agency);</li> 
   <li>specific days when the student trainee(s) will be at Ryerson; </li> 
   <li>student trainee(s) acceptance of the conditions of the unpaid work placement (i.e. Student Declaration of Understanding from the student trainee’s institution); and</li> 
   <li>a signed Letter to Placement Employers (from the student trainee’s institution).</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Provide the Letter to Placement Employers to the Ryerson placement supervisor to sign, and return the signed letter to the student trainee’s institution.</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#f40e3577-92fe-4896-80df-af2d6d6fd273");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1537281815944-responsibilities-of-placement-supervisors" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1537281815944-responsibilities-of-placement-supervisors" aria-controls="accordion-content-1537281815944-responsibilities-of-placement-supervisors" aria-expanded="false">
                            Responsibilities of placement supervisors
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1537281815944-responsibilities-of-placement-supervisors" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1537281815944-responsibilities-of-placement-supervisors">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1537281815944 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="b2420b5a-34ad-4ba0-a7f1-8836e3f2beab" >

    <p>Under the OHSA, a supervisor is a person who has authority over a worker or has control of the activity being performed by a worker in a workplace. This may include a Ryerson University faculty or staff member who provides direct control or supervision of a placement student. Faculty or staff members are considered supervisors under the Ontario Ministry of Labour guidelines, if they do any of the following:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>determine the tasks to be done by a particular placement student;</li> 
 <li>direct and monitor how work is performed on an ongoing basis;</li> 
 <li>decide and schedule hours of work; and/or</li> 
 <li>deal directly with placement students’ occupational health and safety concerns and complaints.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>For a full description, please refer to the definition above.</p> 
<p>The placement supervisor of the student trainee is required to:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Complete and sign the Letter to Placement Employers (provided by the student trainee’s institution), return it to the Ryerson placement coordinator.</li> 
 <li>Complete Ryerson’s <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/environmental-health-safety-elearning.html">Environmental Health and Safety eLearning</a> (online training) and <a href="https://hr.apps.ccs.ryerson.ca/lec/public/event/73">Health and Safety for Managers and Supervisors</a> (in-class training).</li> 
 <li>Familiarize themselves with the supervisor duties under the OHSA, which include: 
  <ul> 
   <li>ensuring that a worker works in the manner, and uses the protected devices; measures and procedures required by the OHSA, and follows the applicable regulations required by the employer;</li> 
   <li>advising the worker of any potential or actual dangers to health or safety you are aware of;</li> 
   <li>providing the worker with written instructions as to the measures and procedures to be taken for their protection; and</li> 
   <li>taking every precaution reasonable in the circumstances for the protection of the worker.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Complete the <a href="https://drive.google.com/open?id=17hp5JHojjod1JpDU7c_wmrzEE_But4zVFhSYkACCvCU">Safety Orientation Checklist for Student Trainees and Learners Working at Ryerson<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</li> 
 <li>Ensure that the student trainee completes the following: 
  <ul> 
   <li>Ryerson <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/environmental-health-safety-elearning.html">Environmental Health and Safety eLearning</a> (online training);</li> 
   <li>Ryerson <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/mandatory-safety-training/whmis.html">Workplace Hazardous Materials Information System (WHMIS)</a> (online training); and</li> 
   <li>other site- or hazard-specific training required on the job.</li> 
   <li><strong>Note</strong>: For high risk work (e.g. work in wet laboratories, machine shops and studios, etc.) student trainees are required to attend Young Worker Awareness training. Please contact Environmental Health and Safety at 416-979-5000, ext. 553770 or <a href="mailto:ehs@ryerson.ca">ehs@ryerson.ca</a> for session dates.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>In the event of an incident or injury, follow the steps under “If a non-Ryerson student trainee has been hurt” on the <a href="/content/ryerson/facilities-management-development/environmental-health-safety/emergencies-reporting/report-incident-injury.html">Report an Incident or Injury page</a>.</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#b2420b5a-34ad-4ba0-a7f1-8836e3f2beab");});</script></div>

